From 8baa82abd93fa519dd9e6fe04619a1f4b5ed1bd7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 11:40:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(session10): add paid launch billing/email/provider
 readiness gates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds a canonical fail-closed readiness model for broad paid SaaS launch.
Pilot readiness remains independent and is not affected by this change.

- services/api/app/paid_launch_readiness.py: new module with
  check_billing_readiness, check_billing_webhook, check_email_readiness,
  check_provider_readiness, and build_paid_launch_readiness. Supports
  Stripe, Paddle (billing); SendGrid, Resend, SMTP (email); EVM_RPC_URL
  (provider). Placeholder detection rejects non-real values. Secret
  values are never included in output.

- services/api/tests/test_paid_launch_readiness.py: 20 focused tests
  covering all 12 required cases (A–L) plus extras for Paddle, Resend,
  field completeness, and unknown provider handling.

- Makefile: adds test-paid-launch-readiness target; validate-paid-ga now
  runs paid launch readiness tests before staging validation.

- .github/workflows/ci-release-gates.yml: adds paid-launch-readiness-gates
  job that runs the Python test suite and uploads a proof artifact.

- generate_guided_simulator_readiness_bundle.py: adds paid_launch_readiness
  section to summary.json artifacts (additive, no existing fields changed).

- docs/PRODUCTION_READINESS_VALIDATION.md, RELEASE_READY.md: Session 10
  sections documenting required env vars, fail-closed logic, how to run
  tests, and the distinction between pilot and paid launch readiness.

